The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Gujarat Narmada Valley Fertilizers Co Ltd has recorded a 64 per cent increase in profit before tax at Rs 116.21 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 71 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous fiscal. The company registered sales of Rs 620.08 crore. Earnings per share stood at Rs 4.88 compared with Rs 3.21 a year ago. 

 Eastern Silk Industries Ltd has registered a net profit of Rs 19.02 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 14.35 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Net sales rose to Rs 124.64 crore from Rs 112.96 crore. Earnings per share were Rs 11.87 compared with Rs 9.25 crore in the year-ago period.

 KSL Realty and Infrastructure Ltd has recorded a 61.12 per cent increase in its net profit at Rs 15.21 crore in the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 9.44 crore in the same quarter of the previous year. Net sales rose 28 per cent to Rs 153.25 crore from Rs 119.72 crore a year ago.

 Larsen amp; Toubro Ltd has bagged an order worth Rs 366 crore from Abu Dhabi Water and Electricity Authority for design, supply, installation and commissioning of two sub-stations at Saadiyat Island. It has bagged another order worth Rs 200 crore from Power Grid Corporation of India Ltd for turnkey construction of extra high-voltage sub-stations. 

 The All India Rubber Industries Association (AIRIA) has entered into an agreement with the Indian Institute of Technology, Kharagpur, to organise an international conference during its India Rubber Expo, 2009. AIRIA is the apex body of the rubber industry.

 Reveleus, a business of i-flex solutions and a global provider of analytical applications for the financial services industry, and Oracle has announced that North Americas SunTrust Banks has selected the Reveleus Basel II Solution as a central component of its planned adherence to the Basel II capital adequacy regulations.

 Era Constructions has changed its name to Era Infra Engineering Limited through a postal ballot. The new name reflects the strategic positioning of the company.

 Tata Indicom has launched Kyocera VLE K122 handset with connection for their prepaid customers. The package is for Rs 1,099. Customers will get a Go Active connection worth Rs 299 with year-long incoming facility.

 VSoft has acquired Bangalore-based software development and consultancy firm Coopman Consultancy Services. The acquisition will add 30 banks to VSofts customer base.

